General.Name: Corella Resources Ltd
General.Description: Corella Resources Ltd engages in the exploration of silica and other minerals. Its flagship property is the Tampu Kaolin project comprises three granted exploration licenses covering an area of approximately 768.03 square kilometers located in north-east of Perth, Western Australia. The company was formerly known as HPAA Pty Ltd and changed its name to Corella Resources Limited in April 2021. Corella Resources Ltd is based in Subiaco, Australia.
General.Address: 40 Subiaco Square Road, Subiaco, WA, Australia, 6008
